Author: able98able98
Content:
aight, soz cuz this gon' be a bit long
In light of the current debaucle that is our (once) beloved country Indonesia, I was thinking about an Indonesian rendering of Les Miserables' "Do You Hear the People Sing?". I find the title to be very apt considering the deafness of our politicians, their cronies, and the law-enforcement force (both brown and green). And it is a very popular protest song. They used it in Hong Kong, , The Philippines, and most recently in South Korea when their president did an oopsie and the whole country got mad. So an Indonesian version would seem very fitting in this climate

Now while I do have *some* background in music, I am pretty limited in other forms of capabilities. So here I am thinking if there are any people in this server is, or know someone who might be fitting, maybe a background in music production, composing, choir, instruments and the creative side like video production and post-production, I am up for some talks and discussion because I feel like this could be a rallying cry to possibly unite the people.

A big ask, I know, and even I still dont have any concrete idea of how it'll work and the logistics and stuff. But I hope this could light the idea, a spark or impetus dare I say, of us as a nation achieving something grander. If, pardon, some tiktok dance and brainrot song can convince nearly 58% of the population to do something a certain way, then why not try this one, or at least give it a thought and entertain the idea for a bit

Sorry for long post. Cheers

Author: nusantarageneral
Content:
1. I think they're already in the right section of the server.

2. It seems that these channels have been used properly and effectively, nevertheless the #‚ä±„Éªüëê„Éª‚Äùpaham‚Äù-thread  seems just a waste of channels tbh and I think we dont actually need the #‚ä±„Éªüëã„Éªintroduction , even though it's nice to introduce yourself to the server and knowing more about someone so you don't offend a fella. As for the #‚ä±„Éªüì∞„Éªglobal-news , it's useful but no discussions about it.

In conclusion:
I suggest that we should remove the #‚ä±„Éªüëê„Éª‚Äùpaham‚Äù-thread and the #‚ä±„Éªüëã„Éªintroduction . If you actually don't need it, up to the mods tbh.

And for the #‚ä±„Éªüì∞„Éªglobal-news , make it's own section, may I give some suggestion for the look of the news and a few branch for it.

1. Geopolitical News
Only news about the geopolitical circumstances nationally and internationally.
Example of news:
https://news.detik.com/internasional/d-7956326/ulah-israel-cegat-kapal-bantuan-untuk-gaza-yang-bawa-thunberg-dan-11-aktivis

2. Economy and Trade News
Only filled with news that are connected to the world/national market, trade, and economical situation right now.
Example of news:
https://www.rri.co.id/daerah/1571945/harga-cabai-masih-tinggi-pasca-idul-adha

3. Unimportant/Entertainment News:
Only news about the world of art, entertainment, culture, and etc.
Example of news:
https://www.idntimes.com/korea/kdrama/drama-korea-tentang-detektif-kepolisian-q9t02-00-v8jyb-mf1zj6

4. News Discussion
Where members of the server discuss only about the news topic they bring. And we can only discuss one news at a time, until a discussion of a news is over, a next one may proceed. And to know if a discussion is over or not, if no one continues a discussion for 20 minutes, a new news discussion may commence. This is to prevent confusion in the discussion
